    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Cookie the Monkey: Home Is Where the Heart Is</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Marilyn Krimm letter urges authorities to consider well-being of monkey named Cookie when considering removal from Brooklyn family (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Family's Monkey Is Rare, and So Is Its Legal Battle'' (front page, July 19):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Family's Monkey Is Rare, and So Is Its Legal Battle'' (front page, July 19):</p>
        <p>My mother was given the gift of a monkey some years before I was born. During her pregnancy she became highly allergic to the monkey, and it was given to the zoo. Within the year it sickened and died. It broke my mother's heart.</p>
        <p>Six years is a long time in the life of a monkey, no matter how endangered. I hope that the authorities take all the parameters of this case into consideration.</p>
        <p>MARILYN KRIMM  Ann Arbor, Mich., July 19, 2000</p>
      </block>
